# Mechvibes: A fun and practical way to bring your favorite keyboard sounds anywhere

> Mechvibes started as a side project I created for myself. Like many mechanical keyboard lovers, I faced challenges when using my keyboard in quiet environments - whether it was late at night or in the office. The loud, satisfying clicks might be music to my ears, but not so much for my parents or coworkers! If you‚Äôre in the same boat, Mechvibes is here for you.

![Mechvibes screenshot](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f0340d8a-3e47-4117-a110-ce54575fc27c)

## What Can You Do with Mechvibes?
üé® **Customize Your Sound Experience:** Add new keyboard sound sets by recording any sound you like. Follow a few simple steps, and you‚Äôre good to go!

üéµ **Enjoy Your Favorite Keyboard Sounds Anywhere:** Use your laptop keyboard or a non-mechanical keyboard at work, and still enjoy the sounds you love.

üåª **Get Creative with Sound Packs:** With Mechvibes Editor, you can create brand-new sound packs, edit existing ones, or even share them with your friends.

üí™ **Versatile Applications:** Use it for anything you can imagine! Demo keyboard sounds for buyers, customize sounds for specific keys, or make your keyboard experience uniquely yours.

> Mechvibes isn‚Äôt just an app, it‚Äôs a way to bring the joy of mechanical keyboards to every environment, without compromising on your surroundings.

## How to Get Started
- Download the app from the [Releases page](https://github.com/hainguyents13/mechvibes/releases/latest)
- Run it.
- Enjoy!

## Compile from Source
Prefer to build the app yourself?
Follow these steps:
- Clone the repository from GitHub.
- Run the appropriate build command for your system:
  - For macOS: `yarn build:mac`
  - For Windows: `yarn build:win`
  - For Linux: `yarn build:linux`

That‚Äôs it, your app is ready to use!

